[It is unusual that almost all (27) of the 31 confirmed human cases of avian influenza A/(H5N1) virus infection in Cambodia have had a fatal outcome, whereas globally, only 371 of the 623 confirmed cases have died. The H5N1 avian influenza virus has affected humans in 15 different countries, whereas the H7N9 avian influenza so far has been confined to China.

The coastal province of Kampot can be located in the map of Cambodia at http://phnompenhtour.com/cambodia-provinces/2.html. - Mod.CP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1iGB.]
